Why am I
getting an MRI?
For most people, the MRI is very safe if you do not
have metal in or on your body. The MRI uses
magnets that can pull on and heat up many types
of metal, and damage things made of metal. You
must take off your watch and jewelry before an
MRI. You should remove makeup, hairspray, and
nail polish, as some of these may be made with
metal. People who have metal in their bodies from
accidents or who have metal implants like cochlear
implants or pacemakers may not be able to have an
MRI. Some types of tattoos or permanent makeup
made with metal may heat up in an MRI and hurt
your skin. You should talk with your doctor about
these issues.
The MRI magnets can also damage computers,
bank cards, and credit cards, so leave them outside
the MRI in a locker or with a family member.
Some people need a special type of dye with an
MRI. If you have a history of severe liver or kidney
problems, or a history of allergy to the dye, you
might not be able to get the dye.
Usually 1 to 1 ½ hours, but it can be much
shorter or longer, depending on what is
ordered. Ask your doctor.
An MRI takes pictures of the inside of your
body that show more detail than other
types of tests, such as X rays or CT
scans.
Yes, the MRI makes a lot of noise as it
works. You will wear earphones or
earplugs in the scanner. ICANSCAN will
give you some examples of MRI sounds.
An MRI does not hurt. Some people find
being in the MRI tube hard because they
do not like to be in a small space. We
hope ICANSCAN will help you get used to
it.
Some people need an injection of dye with
an MRI. Putting the dye in may be a little
uncomfortable for a few moments.
You should be able to go into the scanner
safely. But, if you need an MRI of your
face, sinuses and/or brain, the braces and
retainer might cause big problems with the
MRI picture. Talk about this with your
doctor.
If you could be pregnant, you should talk
with your doctor before the MRI. MRI is
sometimes used in pregnant women, but
the risks are not completely known.
The room is usually kept cold to help the
MRI work well. Most MRI scanners have
blankets if you need them- ask when you
make your appointment.
An MRI scan takes a picture of the inside
of your body. It shows us what the inside
looks like, not what you are thinking or
feeling. The machine makes a lot of noise,
so you will wear earphones so it is not so
loud. You need to go inside a tube to get
the picture, but your mom, dad or other
guardian can stand right outside the tube
and keep you company. You need to be
very still to get a good picture.
